quizzes.question:
Type in an operator to declare an array of integers. The size of the array is 9.
[!raw!]
{0} anArray[{1}];

Fill in the blanks to declare an array of integers containing 9 elements. Assign to each element the value 45 using the for loop.
[!raw!]
int anArray[{0}] ;
for (int x = 0; x <= {1}; x++)
{
 anArray[{2}] = 45;
}

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]Arrays in Loops[/h1]

Let's declare an array, that is going to store 5 integers, and assign a value to each element using the [b]for [/b]loop: [code format="cpp"]int myArr[5];

for(int x=0; x<5; x++) {
  myArr[x] = 42;
}[/code]
Each element in the array is assigned the value of 42.
The [b]x[/b] variable in the for loop is used as the index for the array. 
[note]The last index in the array is 4, so the [b]for [/b]loop condition is x<5.[/note]

